India’s 10-Year Bonds Decline for First Time in Three Days

-- B y   V   R a m a k r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-10-19T03:37:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/india-s-10-year-bonds-decline-for-first-time-in-three-days.html
India ’s 10-year bonds declined for
the first time in three days before a monetary policy review
next week.  The yield on the 7.8 percent note due April 2021 rose two
basis points to 8.77 percent as of 9:05 a.m. in Mumbai,
according to the central bank’s trading system.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
V Ramakrishnan at 
 rvenkatarama@bloomberg.net  